The chairman of Wukari local government area in Taraba state, Mr Adi Daniel, has said eight persons were killed by suspected militia in two locations within the local government on Saturday. He told Daily Trust in a telephone interview that the locations where the eight persons died include Tsukundi and Rafin Kada road – all in Wukari local government area. The chairman said the militia had also blocked Tsukundi road adding that a team of soldiers and police had to be mobilized to the area to chase away the hoodlums. He said he personally accompanied the security agents to the area to ensure normalcy return to the area. Daniel explained that the latest attacks were coming while effort was ongoing to reconcile the two warring factions. He urged the Tiv people to respect the peace agreement reached earlier,  and stop  attacking the Jukun community. “Our people no longer go to farm because of the attacks by Tiv militia in Jukun community,” the chairman claimed. 7 killed in Fresh attacks in two Taraba towns Perennial Tiv/Jukun clashes unsettle Taraba 3 militia caught trying to attack Wukari village Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin